{
  "texts": [
    "Algorithm 3 gives a summary of the above steps upon receipt of an observation y t.",
    "The EnKF can be initialised at time t = 0 by sampling N ensemble members x1:N 0 from p (θ) 0 (•) and setting μ0 and Σ0 to be the sample mean and variance of x1:N 0.",
    "Equations (11)-(13) are applied with μ0 and Σ0 replacing μt|t-1 and Σt|t-1",
    "Up until now, our discussion of the EnKF has assumed that the parameter θ is fixed and known.",
    "In the following three sections, we briefly review some existing methods for dealing with an unknown θ."
  ]
}